    <text>
        <body>
            <div style="handwritten" type="letter" xml:id="d.1">
                <head type="title">István Dobó to Miklós Oláh (Eger, 12 June 1552)</head>
                <floatingText type="regesta">
                    <body>
                        <p xml:id="reg.p.1">1. He has reported to Oláh about what they have heard
                            from the Turkish prisoner both via mail and through Gergely Horváth. The
                            Pasha of Buda returned after he occupied Veszprém, now he is waiting at
                            the field of Rákos to see Kara Ahmed Pasha’s movements before deciding
                            about besieging the castle of Eger. He is rumoured to be building a
                            bridge, and István Losonczy has gone there to fight him. Since Oláh
                            knows well how many men are available to defend the castle, Dobó asks
                            him to send reinforcements. 2. Furthermore, he should instruct Gáspár
                            Pető, István Zolthay, and Márton Káldy to save themselves for defending
                            the castle, and he should instruct the leaders of the county to defend
                            the castle. 3. He is doing what he can, if anything bad still happens,
                            it will not be his fault but due to the fact that there are too few
                            people. He wants to increase the number of infantrymen to 300. He should
                            give a new horse to the young man who is handing this over if his own
                            horse is dead, in order to make sure he can return to him with the news
                            more quickly.</p>
                    </body>
                </floatingText>
                <pb/>
                <p xml:id="p.1">Reverendissime Domine, Domine mihi semper Gratiosissime, servitiorum
                    meorum debitam perpetuamque exhibitionem!<note type="critic" xml:id="note.1">On
                        this letter, see <hi rend="smallcap">Szántó</hi> 1972; and <hi
                            rend="smallcap">Szántó</hi> 1977.</note></p>
                <p xml:id="p.2">[1.] Negotia Turcarum quomodo hic agantur et quo mihi sunt per
                    Turcum captivum relata, Dominationi Vestrae Reverendissimae antea quoque et per
                        postam<note type="critic" xml:id="note.2">See Ep.
                            816.<ref>olahus.tei.15520607_1</ref></note> et per servitorem
                    Dominationis Vestrae Reverendissimae egregium <persName>Gregorium
                        Horwath</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.3">Gergely Horváth
                        (†1552) was cavalryan captain and Dobó’s messenger, see <hi rend="smallcap"
                            >Sugár</hi> 1969, 221; and <hi rend="smallcap">Csiffáry</hi> 2003,
                        292.</note> perscripsi. Qualiterque <persName>Budensis bassa</persName><note
                        type="critic" xml:id="note.4">Hadim Ali Pasha.</note> expugnato
                        <placeName>Vesprimio</placeName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.5"
                        >Veszprém.</note> reversus sit, credo Dominationi Vestrae Reverendissimae
                    apertius quam mihi constare. Nunc est in castris in campo
                        <placeName>Rakos</placeName> certoque mihi nuntiatum est, exspectare dicitur
                    motum <persName>Ahmath bassae</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.6">Kara
                        Ahmed Pasha.</note> et ubi motum illius intelligeret, habere intentionem
                    arcem hanc Dominationis Vestrae Reverendissimae obsidere. Ille vero pontem iam
                    struit super Danubium et dicitur se movisse, contra quem dicitur magnificus
                    dominus <persName>Stephanus de Lossoncz</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.7">István Losonczy.</note> etc., si quid proficere posset,
                    profectus esse. Quare cum Dominatio Vestra Reverendissima aperte intelligit, ego
                    quo numero gentium ad conservationem huius arcis hic sim, regia quoque
                        <persName>maiestas</persName> quantam copiam equitum et peditum ad
                    defensionem eiusdem arcis hic teneat, supplico Dominationi Vestrae
                    Reverendissimae tamquam Domino Gratiosissimo, dignetur eadem Dominatio Vestra
                    Reverendissima de opportuno subsidio quantum ad gentium copiam necesse est, eo
                    modo mature providere, ne in tam amplissima arce prae paucitate gentium
                    inopinate subruamur et (quod Deus avertat) tempore Dominationis Vestrae
                    Reverendissimae per Turcam capiatur. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.3">[2.] Praeterea dignetur Dominatio Vestra Reverendissima dominis
                        <persName>Gaspar Pethew</persName>,<note type="critic" xml:id="note.8"
                        >Gáspár Pető (†after 1561) was Cavalry Officer of Eger castle in 1552, see
                            <hi rend="smallcap">Csiffáry</hi> 2003, 267 and
                        323–324.</note><persName>Stephano Zolthay</persName><note type="critic"
                        xml:id="note.9">István Zoltay was Cavalry Officer of Eger castle in 1552,
                        see <hi rend="smallcap">Csiffáry</hi> 2003, 347–350.</note> et
                        <persName>Martino Kaldy</persName><note type="critic" xml:id="note.10"
                        >Márton Káldy was pedestrian captain, see <hi rend="smallcap">Szántó</hi>
                        1972, 201.</note> capitaneis hic constitutis per litteras mandare, ut et
                    ipsi conservationi arcis se tenere debeant, similiter et ad comitatus superiores
                    litteras dare, ut illi quoque saluti eorum consulendum de maturo subsidio arcis
                    providere curent. </p>
                <p xml:id="p.4">[3.] Ego quantum proficere possum, de eo Dominationi Vestrae
                    Reverendissimae in me nihil diffidat, verum (quod Deus avertat), si quid
                    sinistri huic arci contigerit, protestor <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert"
                        >regiae maiestati et</add> Dominationi Vestrae Reverendissimae non me, sed
                    paucitatem hominum in ea existentem esse in causa. Ego propriori instructioni
                    numerum trecentorum peditum complere curavi, ad conquerendumque pedites centum
                    iam dimisi, pro eo Dominatio Vestra Reverendissima absque ulla mora dignetur
                    super omnibus mihi citissimam <milestone unit="pb"/>facere relationem. Commisi
                    adolescenti meo, ut si etiam equus ubi ad Vestram perveniet, Reverendissima
                    Dominatio, illico morietur, cursu tamen celeri ad eandem Vestram Dominationem
                    Reverendissimam festinare debeat, quod si fit, ut moreretur, dignetur Dominatio
                    Vestra iterum equum alterum adolescenti meo dare, ut citissime redeat. Si etiam
                    ille morietur loco illius quoque, Dominationi Vestrae Reverendissimae alterum
                    dare sum paratus. Tantum est, ut Dominatio Vestra Reverendissima super omnibus
                    mihi informationem citissimam dare dignetur. Restat, quod Dominationem Vestram
                    Reverendissimam felicissime valere desidero.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.5">Datum in <placeName>arce Agriensi</placeName> 12. Iunii anno Domini
                    1552.</p>
                <p xml:id="p.6">Eiusdem Dominationis Vestrae Reverendissimae deditissimus
                    servitor</p>
                <p xml:id="p.7">
                    <seg type="signature">Stephanus Dobo de Rwzka.</seg>
                </p>
                <p xml:id="p.8">
                    <add corresp="Olahus" type="insert">C. Copia litterarum Stephani Dobo.</add>
                </p>
            </div>
